You are working on Mini Cuadre Caja, an ERP/POS Android app.

GENERAL PRINCIPLES
- Preserve architecture consistency.
- Prefer maintainable code over clever code.
- Use minimal diffs.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Explain plan before making major edits.
- If assumptions are needed, state them.

TECH STACK
- Kotlin
- Android Studio
- Jetpack Compose
- Material 3
- Firebase Auth
- Firestore
- Cloud Functions
- Room (offline/local persistence)
- WorkManager (sync jobs)

ARCHITECTURE RULES
- Use MVVM.
- UI layer must be dumb when possible.
- Business rules belong in domain/backend.
- Repositories mediate data sources.
- Prefer use cases for critical flows.
- Avoid tight coupling between features.

ANDROID RULES
- No deprecated APIs.
- Prefer StateFlow over LiveData.
- Use immutable UI state.
- Handle loading, success, error states explicitly.
- Use ViewModel for state management.
- Keep composables small and reusable.
- Use rememberSaveable when appropriate.

JETPACK COMPOSE RULES
- Stateless composables when possible.
- Hoist state upward.
- Use Material 3 components.
- Respect spacing and readability.
- Optimize for fast cashier interactions.
- Avoid deeply nested composables.

FIREBASE RULES
- Never trust client for critical calculations.
- Validate critical actions in Cloud Functions.
- Firestore writes should be explicit and typed.
- Prefer server timestamps where needed.
- Keep security rules in mind before schema changes.

OFFLINE RULES
- App must remain usable without internet when possible.
- Queue syncable actions.
- Do not block user unnecessarily on network failures.
- Surface sync state clearly.

FINANCIAL DOMAIN RULES
- Do not mutate historical financial events.
- Closures must be auditable.
- Cash movements and accounting operations are different concepts.
- Preserve traceability.

CODE QUALITY
- Prefer descriptive names.
- Remove dead code.
- Avoid duplication.
- Add comments only when they add value.
- If refactoring, preserve behavior unless requested.

WHEN IMPLEMENTING FEATURES
- First inspect affected modules.
- Reuse existing patterns.
- Mention files to change before editing.
- If feature conflicts with architecture, warn first.

WHEN FIXING BUGS
- Diagnose root cause first.
- Patch minimally.
- Mention likely regression risks.

OUTPUT STYLE
- Be concise.
- Show reasoning in bullets.
- Show changed files list.
